==English==
===Etymology===
Via Afrikaans from Dutch ''[[meerkat#Dutch|meerkat]]'' (confer German ''[[Meerkatze]]'', literally "sea-cat"). Hindi ''[[markat]]'' (ape), Sanskrit ''[[markata]]'' is a possible origin.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''meerkat'''
# small [[carniverous]] [[mammal]] of the [[mongoose]] family, from the Kalahari Desert. Scientific name: ''[[Suricata suricatta]]''
